        Import the the table definitions from an EDS XML formatted file
        Specified by:
        importFromFile in interface CcddImportExportInterface
        Parameters:
        importFile - reference to the user-specified XML input file
        importType - ImportType.IMPORT_ALL to import the table type, data type, and macro definitions, and the data from all the table definitions; ImportType.FIRST_DATA_ONLY to load only the data for the first table defined
        targetTypeDefn - table type definition of the table in which to import the data; ignored if importing all tables
        ignoreErrors - true to ignore all errors in the import file
        replaceExistingMacros - not used for EDS import
        replaceExistingGroups - not used for EDS import
        Throws:
        CcddClassesDataTable.CCDDException - If a data is missing, extraneous, or in error in the import file
        java.io.IOException - If an import file I/O error occurs
        java.lang.Exception - If an unanticipated error occurs

      • exportToFile

        public void exportToFile​(CcddClassesComponent.FileEnvVar exportFile,
                         java.lang.String[] tableNames,
                         boolean includeBuildInformation,
                         boolean replaceMacros,
                         boolean includeAllTableTypes,
                         boolean includeAllDataTypes,
                         boolean includeAllInputTypes,
                         boolean includeAllMacros,
                         boolean includeReservedMsgIDs,
                         boolean includeProjectFields,
                         boolean includeGroups,
                         boolean includeAssociations,
                         boolean includeVariablePaths,
                         CcddVariableHandler variableHandler,
                         java.lang.String[] separators,
                         java.lang.Object... extraInfo)
                  throws javax.xml.bind.JAXBException,
                         javax.xml.bind.MarshalException,
                         java.lang.Exception
        Export the project in EDS XML format to the specified file
        Specified by:
        exportToFile in interface CcddImportExportInterface
        Parameters:
        exportFile - reference to the user-specified output file
        tableNames - array of table names to convert
        includeBuildInformation - true to include the CCDD version, project, host, and user information
        replaceMacros - * Not used for EDS export (all macros are expanded) * true to replace any embedded macros with their corresponding values
        includeAllTableTypes - * Not used for EDS export * true to include the all table type definitions in the export file
        includeAllDataTypes - * Not used for EDS export * true to include the all data type definitions in the export file
        includeAllInputTypes - * Not used for XTCE export * true to include the all user-defined input type definitions in the export file
        includeAllMacros - * Not used for EDS export * true to include the all macro definitions in the export file
        includeReservedMsgIDs - * Not used for EDS export * true to include the contents of the reserved message ID table in the export file
        includeProjectFields - * Not used for EDS export * true to include the project-level data field definitions in the export file
        includeGroups - * Not used for EDS export * true to include the groups and group data field definitions in the export file
        includeAssociations - * Not used for EDS export * true to include the script associations in the export file
        includeVariablePaths - * Not used for EDS export * true to include the variable path for each variable in a structure table, both in application format and using the user-defined separator characters
        variableHandler - variable handler class reference; null if includeVariablePaths is false
        separators - * Not used for EDS export * string array containing the variable path separator character(s), show/hide data types flag ('true' or 'false'), and data type/variable name separator character(s); null if includeVariablePaths is false
        extraInfo - [0] endianess (EndianType.BIG_ENDIAN or EndianType.LITTLE_ENDIAN)
        [1] are the telemetry and command headers big endian (true or false)
        Throws:
        javax.xml.bind.JAXBException - If an error occurs marshaling the project
        java.lang.Exception - If an unanticipated error occurs
        javax.xml.bind.MarshalException
